{
  "texts": [
    "For English learners of Azerbaijani, listening to native Azerbaijani speakers can help them better understand the language's syllable structure and stress patterns.",
    "To further mitigate the challenges posed by phonetic differences, the following strategies can be employed:",
    "Targeted Pronunciation Practice: Both groups of learners should engage in targeted pronunciation practice that focuses on their specific weaknesses.",
    "For Azerbaijani speakers, practice should include mastering English vowel distinctions and consonant clusters, while English speakers need focused exercises on producing Azerbaijani fricatives and adhering to vowel harmony rules.",
    "This can be achieved through repetitive practice and feedback from teachers or software."
  ]
}